Serafina has never had a reason to disobey her pa and venture beyond the grounds of Biltmore Estate. There''s plenty to explore in Mr. and Mrs. Vanderbilt''s vast and opulent home, but she must take care to never be seen. None of the rich folk upstairs know that Serafina exists; she and her pa have lived in the basement for as long as Serafina can remember. She has learned to prowl through the darkened corridors at night, to sneak and hide, using the mansion''s hidden doors and secret passageways.

But when children at the estate start disappearing, only Serafina knows the clues to follow. A mysterious man in a black cloak stalks Biltmore''s corridors at night. Following her own harrowing escape, Serafina risks everything by joining forces with Braeden Vanderbilt, the young nephew of Biltmore''s owners. Braeden and Serafina must uncover the Man in the Black Cloak''s true identity before all of the children vanish one by one.', 'A hidden girl at Biltmore Estate uncovers a dark mystery as children vanish, hunted by a sinister man in a black cloak.', 2015, '133803765X', '9781484711873', 320, NULL, NULL, 'https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/id/8763233-L.jpg', '/works/OL20101417W', NULL, 'Jun 14, 2016', 'English', NULL, 1, 0, 'serafina-and-the-black-cloak-robert-beatty', 1, 'openlibrary', NULL, 0, NULL, 'public', '2026-03-21 17:27:44', '2026-03-23 04:16:26');
